## Ingredients
- 2 tbsp oil
- 1 tsp cumin seeds
- 1 tsp curry powder
- 1/2 tsp turmeric
- 1 tsp salt
- 1/2 tsp black pepper
- 1 inch ginger, grated
- 1 small cauliflower, cut into florets
- 2 tbsp fresh coriander, chopped
- zest of 1 lime

## Method
1. Preheat oven to 220°C.
2. In a large bowl, mix oil, cumin seeds, curry powder, turmeric, salt, and black pepper.
3. Add the cauliflower florets and toss to coat evenly.
4. Spread the coated cauliflower on a baking tray in a single layer.
5. Roast for 10–15 minutes until golden and tender.
6. Finish with grated ginger, lime zest, and chopped coriander before serving.

## Notes
- Adjust spice levels to suit your taste.
- Pair with a side of basmati rice or naan.
- Store leftovers in an airtight container for up to 3 days.
